---
title: Plantain and Black Bean Tostadas with Pickled Red Onion, Avocado, and Feta
description: Plantains are a staple of Latin and South American cuisine— used both in their ripe and unripe forms. Ripe, nearly black plantains can be fried into maduros. Starchy and slightly sweet, maduros are the star of these tostadas. Paired with the bite of pickled onion, the creaminess of avocado, and smoky cumin, each bite has the perfect balance of flavor.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/plantain-and-black-bean-tostadas-w22-8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plantain-and-black-bean-tostadas-8b4567.pdf
